<div id="review_1033529881" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1033529881" />
    <a title="Vanessa Baez-dudley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7929630-vanessa-baez-dudley"><img alt="Vanessa Baez-dudley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1330251393p2/7929630.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1033529881?book_show_action=true">Aug 22, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vanessa Baez-dudley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vanessa Baez-dudley" href="/user/show/7929630-vanessa-baez-dudley">Vanessa Baez-dudley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781481248341" href="/book/show/17444140-a-punctual-paymaster">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1033529881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11239651160668717240">Excellent Novel of Tragedy and Triumph in the 1930’s<br/><br/>The vivid southern imagery, heavy racism, and proud families are what makes this novel something to recommend to your children and their children. From the start of the story you are pulled into dangerous times, where the wrong words from colored people could easily get you beat to death. The town of Delphi is split into two regions (North and South), where two families preside over one each. You have Nikkos Thanos, who is the rich white owner </span>
  <span id="freeText11239651160668717240" style="display:none">Excellent Novel of Tragedy and Triumph in the 1930’s<br /><br />The vivid southern imagery, heavy racism, and proud families are what makes this novel something to recommend to your children and their children. From the start of the story you are pulled into dangerous times, where the wrong words from colored people could easily get you beat to death. The town of Delphi is split into two regions (North and South), where two families preside over one each. You have Nikkos Thanos, who is the rich white owner of everything from the lumber mill to the casket company in the North. Then you have Thaddeus “Cousin” Taylor, who is a grocery store owner in the south and is highly revered in the black community. Of course as time goes on you end up following the daughter and grandson of these two individuals. Throughout the entire book I kept wondering what the title was about but of course you don’t find out until the very end. But it was well worth the wait! The author has a way with words that bring you in and make you feel his words. I wanted to cry when tragedy struck and I wanted to sing to the heavens when victory was achieved! The world-building was phenomenal and I felt as though I was walking down the dirt roads in the town in the 1930’s with my bucket of worms and a fishing pole. Excellent novel and I highly recommend it to young teenagers. Especially during these uncertain times of discord in our own streets today. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11239651160668717240" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


