<div id="review_1129933117" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1129933117" />
    <a title="Janel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15566052-janel"><img alt="Janel" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1129933117?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janel" href="/user/show/15566052-janel">Janel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781481248341" href="/book/show/17444140-a-punctual-paymaster">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1129933117" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6270378273153020017">The Punctual Paymaster is the incredible debut novel by Dan Groat. This book has heart and soul and is the type of novel that really leaves one thinking about life and the bigger picture. I agree with many other reviewers that this is one of the best books that I have read this year, or in the past couple of years to be honest. The author has a great grasp of the use of dialogue and he has some of the better dialogue I have seen recently. His characters are well developed, as is the story. There</span>
  <span id="freeText6270378273153020017" style="display:none">The Punctual Paymaster is the incredible debut novel by Dan Groat. This book has heart and soul and is the type of novel that really leaves one thinking about life and the bigger picture. I agree with many other reviewers that this is one of the best books that I have read this year, or in the past couple of years to be honest. The author has a great grasp of the use of dialogue and he has some of the better dialogue I have seen recently. His characters are well developed, as is the story. There is no sense of black or white but keeps to the gray, which really lends authenticity to the book and gives it a real hold on reality. I am really looking forward to reading more from this author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6270378273153020017" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


